Detailed Description

Structure containing input parameters for OCMC ECC software test.

Field Documentation

uint32_t DiagLib_EccOcmcTestParams::eccOcmcEdmaChNum

EDMA params are required for writing 128 bits of data at once. This is because ECC is calculated for 128bit data. Otherwise ECC value would change if 32bits are written.Channel number for EDMA transfer.

uint32_t DiagLib_EccOcmcTestParams::eccOcmcEdmaEvtqNum

Event queue number for EDMA transfer.

uint32_t DiagLib_EccOcmcTestParams::eccOcmcEdmaTccNum

Channel number on which EDMA transfer completion interrupt is generated

uint32_t DiagLib_EccOcmcTestParams::eccOcmcMode

OCMC controller mode of operation. Refer enum DiagLib_EccOcmcModes_t.

uint32_t DiagLib_EccOcmcTestParams::eccOcmcRamErrAddr

Address of OCMC ECC region where the error can be introduced.
